00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,559
Went straight back into that meeting room.

303
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:48,200
So lots of lessons along the way, what I can do better,

304
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:49,840
how I can be a better person.

305
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:53,919
And, you know, we all put up with difficult situations

306
00:14:53,919 --> 00:14:57,200
and I think you've got to embrace those challenges

307
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,860
and keep moving forward.

308
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:03,399
But if we all accept those and we continue them,

309
00:15:04,259 --> 00:15:05,580
then that's terrible.

310
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:09,899
But if we go through those situations and resolve to do better

311
00:15:09,899 --> 00:15:11,159
as a result of them,

312
00:15:11,159 --> 00:15:12,080
then that's good.

313
00:15:12,759 --> 00:15:15,399
And it's always been one of my...

314
00:15:15,399 --> 00:15:17,759
If you're a have-a-goer, you know you're going to have lots of failures

315
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:18,659
and make mistakes.

316
00:15:19,059 --> 00:15:21,820
But it's what you learn from those situations

317
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:25,639
that gives you the 10 steps forward I was talking about earlier.

318
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:28,340
If you actually take the time to recognise it,

319
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:30,659
get the value from it and move forward.

