00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,460
Everybody says take risks, take risks.

402
00:19:32,579 --> 00:19:33,039
That's great.

403
00:19:33,819 --> 00:19:37,339
But the corollary of that is you've got to find ways

404
00:19:37,339 --> 00:19:40,519
of de-risking yourself so that other people can take

405
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:43,720
a risk with you or take a risk on you.

406
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:49,640
And so I spend a lot of time now preparing ahead of big decisions

407
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:53,640
or big interviews that I'm doing or big opportunities I'm pursuing,

408
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:57,640
looking really across other people's perspectives,

409
00:19:58,019 --> 00:20:01,259
understanding the circumstances and then presenting in a way

410
00:20:01,259 --> 00:20:05,299
that de-risks, whether it's myself or the issue or the proposition.

